<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-633] Update the release process to use maven plugins</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-633</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The release process for OpenJPA is currently quite long and involves a lot of manual steps. When we first entered the incubator this was required, however there are a lot of new plugins for Maven which may make all our lives easier. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally our release instructions would look more like Geronimo&apos;s : &lt;a href=&quot;http://cwiki.apache.org/GMOxPMGT/geronimo-release-process.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://cwiki.apache.org/GMOxPMGT/geronimo-release-process.html&lt;/a&gt; which takes advantage of the maven release plugin and gpg plugins. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resolving this completely may take some time. In the meantime the old release process will work and can be used if we need to cut a new release. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
